INSERT INTO [dbo].[BudgetProjectJustifications] ([ProjectCostID], [IsSubmitted], [ProjectManager], [ProjectName], [Description], [Justification], [CreatedOn]) VALUES (49, 0, N'bjones', N'E100 - Motor Maintenance', N'This is the continuation of Explorer’s annual motor maintenance program.  This program is to systematically inspect, clean and do minor repairs to the electrical motors.  While we are planning to do eight (8) motors, two (2) on the 28” line, one (1) on 12” line from Greenville, two (2) on the 24” line and three (3) on the- 10” line; priorities may be shifted to other motors to respond to unforeseen issues. These motor repairs will be done in the Houston, Arlington, Greenville, Glenpool, Wood River, and Hammond districts.', N'Good Idea', '20151104')
INSERT INTO [dbo].[BudgetProjectJustifications] ([ProjectCostID], [IsSubmitted], [ProjectManager], [ProjectName], [Description], [Justification], [CreatedOn]) VALUES (50, 0, N'jduvall', N'E101 - VFD Maintenance', N'This is a multi-year project to provide for scheduled and unscheduled VFD maintenance on twelve (12) VFD’s. This work will be performed in the Port Arthur, Houston, Greenville, Glenpool and Wood River districts.', N'Good Idea', '20151104')
INSERT INTO [dbo].[BudgetProjectJustifications] ([ProjectCostID], [IsSubmitted], [ProjectManager], [ProjectName], [Description], [Justification], [CreatedOn]) VALUES (51, 0, N'lmcneely', N'E103 - Pump Maintenance', N'Pump Maintenance-E103   The work generally includes rotating assembly change-outs and repairs, pump case repairs, and associated equipment included with a major repair.  This is proposed as a continuation of the multi-year project initiated in 1990 to perform required major/preventative maintenance on Explorer’s pumps.  Due to replacement during expansion 28 of the original 28” and 24” pipeline pumps have been replaced and 5 rebuilt.  Repairs will be required on pumps which have not been replaced.       There are approximately 20 total recommended major pump maintenance projects required to keep the Explorer pumps within a 25-year review period.  This proposal recommends these projects be completed within a 5-year period.  This strategy calls for 4+ pump maintenance projects per year for the next 5 years in an attempt to move back to a regularly scheduled major pump maintenance program. The 2015 plan consists of:    Conroe #1 (Sulzer w/ 5500 HP):         Field report in 2008 Repair rotating assembly, especially shaft Chatsworth#1                                     From master plan list below Plantersville #2                                    Complete partial repair begun in 2011. Wood River #9                                   Rebuild and upgrade this pump to meet planned increases in transfer needs                      Project Justification:       Project Cost:              $ 500,000 (See details below)     2016 Preventative / Major Pump Maintenance Program   1.         Inspect and Repair - $100,000 Conroe #1, Bingham 24 x 24 x 34A HSB 1 stage                         Field report in 2008 Repair rotating assembly, especially shaft   2.         Inspect and Repair - $100,000                         Chatsworth Unit #1 United 14 x 28 DVS 1 stage This pump has not been opened and inspected since installation in 1978.  This pump should be inspected for damage and rotating assembly wear.  It has also experienced problems locking up.     3.         Inspect and Repair - $100,000                         Plantersville #2, 10” line, United 4 x 11 MSN S4A1, 4 stage centrifugal pump.                          This pump failed in summer 2011 and is need of shop DCI and repair.   4.         Inspect and Repair – $125,000                         Wood River #9, Bingham 14 x 14 12.5 HSB 1 stage, delivery pump. This pump will see increased usage as BD projects mature and come on-line.  Overdue inspection and overhaul by several years.    Multi-Year Preventative / Major Pump Maintenance Schedule       2016  CON 1 $100,000  CHA 1 $100,000  PLN 1 $100,000  WDR 9 $125,000  On-demand $75,000     $500,000   2017  WDR 5  CHA 2  GVL 7  WDR 1  On-demand         $100,000  $100,000  $100,000  $100,000  $150,000  550,000   2018  GLN 1  GVL 8  CHA 2  DEC 1  On-demand         $150,000  $100,000  $100,000  $100,000  $150,000  600,000   2019  PTA 1  GLN 7  HMD 1  GRP 1  On-demand         $100,000  $100,000  $100,000  $100,000  $150,000  550,000   2020  WR 7  GRP 5  WDR 1  GRP 5  On-demand         $100,000  $100,000  $100,000  $100,000  $150,000  550,000     5 YEAR PLAN TOTAL:       2,750,000   E103_15Pump Maintenance.doc LBM 7/1/15   ·         Refer to Policy E-400 for Economic Analysis Requirements ·         Attach EPL-8917C (Capital) and EPL-8917E (Expense) estimate work sheets.', N'Good Idea', '20151104')
INSERT INTO [dbo].[BudgetProjectJustifications] ([ProjectCostID], [IsSubmitted], [ProjectManager], [ProjectName], [Description], [Justification], [CreatedOn]) VALUES (52, 0, N'lmcneely', N'E104 - Pump Base & Pipe Strain Repairs', N'This is a multiyear project to fill voids in pump unit bases with epoxy grout, to check bases for stability and rigidity, to stabilize as required, and to modify piping to reduce piping strain on pump units.   Voids will be filled with epoxy grout to the extent possible to eliminate water or oil accumulation within the base. Bases which are found to be moving on the foundation will be secured by removing and repouring the base with new grout or using epoxy grout, rebar, and additional anchor bolts by removing portions of the foundation cap and existing cement grout, drilling and inserting rebar ties into the foundation, inserting a new anchor bolt at this area, and filling this area with epoxy grout to serve as a key lock between the foundation and the base.   Pipe strain will be eliminated by adjusting adjacent flanges (if possible) or modification of the appropriate piping, depending on the condition.  No pump base work was performed in 2012.  Claremore units 1 and 2 bases were repairs and re-grouted with motor rails milled to restore to level and to accommodate spare motor footing.   In 2015, multiple sites were inspected which identified several bases with voids, several with grout repairs required and some cosmetic issues.  Major repair of Pt Arthur Units 7 and 8 were completed in early 2015.  Repairs to pump and motor bases from PTA to CLA are scheduled for 2016.     Pipe strain will be checked everytime a pump is removed for maintenance and the data recorded for future use in this program..', N'Good Idea', '20151104')
INSERT INTO [dbo].[BudgetProjectJustifications] ([ProjectCostID], [IsSubmitted], [ProjectManager], [ProjectName], [Description], [Justification], [CreatedOn]) VALUES (53, 0, N'dyanchunas', N'E106 - Fire Water System Maintenance', N'To evaluate and maintain the current fire water systems at some of the Explorer Pipeline Locations.  To include Port Arthur, Fauna, Greenville, Arlington, Glenpool, Wood River, and Hammond.', N'Good Idea', '20151104')
